  "body": "(This issue was discovered and diagnosed by @wighawag in [solidity-coverage 573][1])\r\n\r\nIn the compile task, the location of sources is read from the config object. For example here:\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/6ffb8baf0ede8c8c73b502bba826b0f8196604b2/packages/hardhat-core/src/builtin-tasks/compile.ts#L112\r\n\r\nThis allows a task to modify solidity files, store them in a temporary location, and direct the compiler to use them as inputs by changing the value of `config.paths.sources`.\r\n\r\nHowever `paths.artifacts` does not seem configurable in the same way because it's set like this:  \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/6ffb8baf0ede8c8c73b502bba826b0f8196604b2/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/runtime-environment.ts#L77\r\n\r\nThis means a task can't write comp. artifacts to a temporary location and direct subsequent tasks to read from there.\r\n\r\nsolidity-coverage tries to set the sources, artifacts and cache paths, hoping these will be dynamically read.\r\n \r\n[1]: https://github.com/sc-forks/solidity-coverage/issues/573",
