    "body": "That's a good question. I think it makes sense to have a different, temporary artifacts directory _if that's the only way to do something_.\r\n\r\nBut I feel that, ideally, that shouldn't be necessary: if they are temporary, maybe the real problem is that there's not an easy way to use them in-memory for the duration of a task without writing them down to disk.\r\n\r\nPut another way: do you see a different change that would let you do what you want to do _without_ having to rely on writing temporary artifacts to disk?",
